- "Stand out the most" implies the products with the highest price difference from the average price of products in the same brand and category;
- The average price is calculated for each combination of brand and category;
- The ranking is done within each brand and category.

- The average rating is a measure of the product's overall quality as perceived by users;
- The comparison count indicates how often the product is considered in user comparisons;
- The price update count reflects how frequently the product's price has changed.

- 'Top-rated' refers to the highest average rating given by users;
- 'Key specifications' include the primary attributes that define a product's performance, display, battery, etc.;
- 'Price' is the current price of the product as recorded in the price history.

- 'Shining like stars' refers to products with the highest average ratings;
- 'Current and previous prices' indicate the latest and the most recent previous prices of the products;
- 'Number of reviews' represents the total count of reviews each product has received.

- 'Moving average price' refers to the average price of a product over a sliding window of the last 11 price updates;
- 'Cumulative rating' refers to the sum of all ratings a product has received over time;
- 'Recent bloom after the dawn of 2022' means the product was released after January 1, 2022;
- 'Unbroken stem' means the product is not discontinued;
- 'Second-tier garden' refers to a category that is a subcategory of a top-level category in the category hierarchy.

- 'More expensive laptops' refers to laptops priced above the average price of all laptops in the same category;
- 'Recently released' refers to products released between January 1, 2020, and January 1, 2023;
- 'Still available' indicates that the product is not discontinued.

- "blossomed with a radiant reputation" refers to products with an average rating greater than 3;
- "ample stock" refers to products with a total quantity in stock greater than 50;
- "frequent comparisons" refers to products that have been compared more than 5 times;
- "average price of their respective categories" refers to the average price of the category to which the product belongs.

- "shining star" refers to the product with the highest average rating;
- "praise from its admirers" refers to the average rating given by product reviewers;
- "at least five reviews" means the product must have a minimum of 5 reviews to be considered.

- "genuine admirers" refers to verified purchasers;
- "exceptional qualities" refers to products with an average rating greater than 4;
- "blossoms" is a metaphor for products;
- "vast garden of products" is a metaphor for the product database.

- "blossoms" refers to products;
- "favored by the bees" refers to products with an average rating greater than 3;
- "having petals left in the garden" refers to products with a total quantity in stock greater than 0.
